---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import PageHeader from "../components/Sections/PageHeader.astro";

const lastUpdated = "12 July 2026";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Service - Blue Fox Tours"
  description="The terms that govern my guided tours"
>
  <PageHeader
    title="Terms of Service"
    subtitle="The terms that govern my guided tours"
    backgroundImage="/uploads/tours-header-bg.jpg"
  />

  <section class="section-y">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-8"><em>Last updated: {lastUpdated}</em></p>

        <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold mb-4">1. Who I am</h2>
        <p class="text-l text-gray-700 mb-2">
          These terms govern the guided tour services provided by:
        </p>
        <p class="text-l text-gray-700 mb-6">
          <strong>Filip Huta – Blue Fox Tours</strong><br />
          Registered address: TODO_ADDRESS<br />
          IČO (Business ID): TODO_ICO<br />
          Licensed Prague tour guide (Tour Guide ID, class II)<br />
          Email: <a href="mailto:info@bluefoxtours.cz" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700">info@bluefoxtours.cz</a>
          | Phone: <a href="tel:+420773537656" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700">+420 773 537 656</a>
        </p>
        <p class="text-l text-gray-700 mb-10">
          I provide <strong>guiding services only</strong>. I am not a travel agency or tour operator
          within the meaning of Czech Act No. 159/1999 Sb.; I do not sell package tours, accommodation,
          or transport. Where a tour involves public transport (for example, the train to Terezín),
          fares are paid by you directly and are not part of my service — I simply help you buy the
          right tickets and travel with you.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold mb-4">2. What you're booking</h2>
        <p class="text-l text-gray-700 mb-6">
          All tours are private: your group and me. Each tour's page states its duration, route, what
          is included in the price, and what is not. Unless a tour page says otherwise, prices do
          <strong>not</strong> include food, drinks, transport fares, or admission fees. Prices are
          quoted in EUR <strong>per group</strong>, not per person, according to the group-size tiers
          on each tour page.
        </p>
        <p class="text-l text-gray-700 mb-10">
          Routes and content may be adjusted on the day for weather, closures, crowds, or your group's
          interests — that flexibility is a feature of a private tour, not a defect. The substance of
          the tour will always be delivered.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold mb-4">3. How booking works</h2>
        <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 text-l text-gray-700 mb-6 space-y-2">
          <li>You send a booking request through the website form, by email, or by WhatsApp.</li>
          <li>I confirm availability and details in writing, normally within 24 hours.</li>
          <li>The contract between us is concluded when I send you a written confirmation of your booking.</li>
        </ol>
        <p class="text-l text-gray-700 mb-10">
          If you book through a third-party platform (Viator, GetYourGuide, or similar), that platform's
          booking, payment, and cancellation terms apply to your booking instead of sections 3–5 of
          these terms.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold mb-4">4. Payment</h2>
        <p class="text-l text-gray-700 mb-10">
          For direct bookings, payment is due at the end of the tour, in cash (CZK or EUR) or by card
          via SumUp (Visa, Mastercard, American Express, Apple Pay, Google Pay — see the Contact page
          for the current list). For the Theresienstadt tour, admission fees are included in the price
          and covered by me.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold mb-4">5. Cancellations and changes</h2>
        <p class="text-l text-gray-700 mb-6">
          <strong>By you:</strong> You may cancel or request to reschedule free of charge up to
          <strong>24 hours</strong> before the tour's start time. For cancellations less than 24 hours
          before the start, or if you do not show up, I reserve the right to charge 100% of the tour
          price. Arriving late reduces your tour time; if you have not arrived within 30 minutes of the
          agreed start and I cannot reach you, the booking is treated as a no-show.
        </p>
        <p class="text-l text-gray-700 mb-6">
          <strong>By me:</strong> If I must cancel — illness, family emergency, or conditions that would
          make the tour unsafe — I will tell you as soon as possible and offer you an alternative date
          or a full refund of anything you have paid. Tours run in rain or shine; please dress for the
          weather. I am not responsible for delays or cancellations of public transport, or for
          unexpected closures of third-party sites, though I will always do my best to adapt the
          itinerary so you still get a full experience.
        </p>
        <p class="text-l text-gray-700 mb-10">
          <strong>Statutory withdrawal right:</strong> Under § 1837(j) of the Czech Civil Code
          (implementing EU consumer law), the 14-day right of withdrawal for distance contracts does
          <strong>not</strong> apply to leisure services provided on a specific date — which is what a
          tour booking is. Your cancellation rights are those described above, which are more generous
          than the legal minimum.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold mb-4">6. Your part of the deal</h2>
        <p class="text-l text-gray-700 mb-6">
          You are responsible for your own safety, belongings, and travel insurance, and for following
          basic safety guidance during the tour (we will be walking on cobblestones, across busy
          streets, and in crowded places). <strong>Children remain under the supervision and
          responsibility of their parents or accompanying adults at all times</strong>, including at
          playgrounds visited during the Prague with Children Tour. Please tell me in advance about any
          mobility limitations or, for the children's tour, allergies — snacks are pre-packaged and
          agreed with parents beforehand (see the
          <a href="/privacy-policy" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700">Privacy Policy</a>
          for how allergy information is handled).
        </p>
        <p class="text-l text-gray-700 mb-10">
          I may end a tour without refund in the extreme case of aggressive, unlawful, or severely
          intoxicated behavior that makes the tour impossible to deliver safely. In fifteen years of
          guiding I have never needed this clause; it exists so that we both know where we stand.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold mb-4">7. Tour materials</h2>
        <p class="text-l text-gray-700 mb-10">
          Worksheets, booklets, brochures, and all tour content and commentary are my intellectual
          property. They are yours to keep and enjoy as a participant, but may not be reproduced or
          distributed commercially without my permission. Audio or video recording of the full tour for
          publication requires my prior consent — photos and short clips for personal use and social
          media are always welcome.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold mb-4">8. Complaints and disputes</h2>
        <p class="text-l text-gray-700 mb-6">
          If anything about your tour disappoints you, please tell me — ideally during or right after
          the tour, when I can still fix it, or by email afterwards. I take this seriously; it's a
          one-person business and my reputation is the whole company.
        </p>
        <p class="text-l text-gray-700 mb-10">
          If you are a consumer and we cannot resolve a dispute between ourselves, you have the right to
          out-of-court dispute resolution through the <strong>Czech Trade Inspection Authority (Česká
          obchodní inspekce, ČOI)</strong>, Štěpánská 796/44, 110 00 Praha 1,
          <a href="https://www.coi.cz" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700">www.coi.cz</a>
          /
          <a href="https://adr.coi.cz" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700">adr.coi.cz</a>.
          You may also use the EU online dispute resolution platform at
          <a href="https://ec.europa.eu/consumers/odr" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700">ec.europa.eu/consumers/odr</a>.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold mb-4">9. Governing law</h2>
        <p class="text-l text-gray-700 mb-10">
          These terms and any contract between us are governed by the law of the Czech Republic. If you
          are a consumer, this does not deprive you of protections granted by the mandatory consumer law
          of your country of residence.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold mb-4">10. Changes to these terms</h2>
        <p class="text-l text-gray-700">
          I may update these terms from time to time; the version published on this website at the
          moment of your booking confirmation is the one that applies to your booking.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
